            <bioghist>
                <p>United States Insole Co. of Chicago, Illinois, were manufacturers of magnetic
                    goods of all kinds, including belts, caps, jackets, and insoles. The company's
                    motto was "Magnetism the source of life."</p>
            </bioghist>

            <scopecontent>
                <p>This is a circular letter, dated 1886, from the United States Insole Co. to
                    representatives of the Brotherhood of Locomotive Workers. The letter requests
                    names and addresses of locomotive workers and offers a free pair of magnetic
                    insoles in exchange for this information.</p>
            </scopecontent>


